a.xlink:title: CountingGreyboxFuzzer class hierarchy
class CountingGreyboxFuzzer: Count how often individual paths are exercised.
run(self, runner: MutationFuzzer.FunctionCoverageRunner) -> Tuple[Any, str]: Inform scheduler about path frequency
reset(self): Reset path frequency
class GreyboxFuzzer: Coverage-guided mutational fuzzing.

run(self, runner: MutationFuzzer.FunctionCoverageRunner) -> Tuple[Any, str]: Run function(inp) while tracking coverage. If we reach new coverage, add inp to population and its coverage to population_coverage
reset(self): Reset the initial population, seed index, coverage information
class AdvancedMutationFuzzer: Base class for mutation-based fuzzing.

__init__(self, seeds: List[str], mutator: Mutator, schedule: PowerSchedule) -> None: Constructor. `seeds` - a list of (input) strings to mutate. `mutator` - the mutator to apply. `schedule` - the power schedule to apply.
fuzz(self) -> str: Returns first each seed once and then generates new inputs
create_candidate(self) -> str: Returns an input generated by fuzzing a seed in the population
reset(self) -> None: Reset the initial population and seed index
class Fuzzer: Base class for fuzzers.
__init__(self) -> None: Constructor
fuzz(self) -> str: Return fuzz input
run(self, runner: Fuzzer.Runner = <Fuzzer.Runner object at 0x10fcf1f10>) -> Tuple[subprocess.CompletedProcess, str]: Run `runner` with fuzz input
runs(self, runner: Fuzzer.Runner = <Fuzzer.PrintRunner object at 0x10fcf14f0>, trials: int = 10) -> List[Tuple[subprocess.CompletedProcess, str]]: Run `runner` with fuzz input, `trials` times
class AFLFastSchedule: Exponential power schedule as implemented in AFL
__init__(self, exponent: float) -> None: Constructor
assignEnergy(self, population: collections.abc.Sequence) -> None: Assign exponential energy inversely proportional to path frequency
class PowerSchedule: Define how fuzzing time should be distributed across the population.
__init__(self) -> None: Constructor
assignEnergy(self, population: collections.abc.Sequence) -> None: Assigns each seed the same energy
choose(self, population: collections.abc.Sequence) -> Seed: Choose weighted by normalized energy.
normalizedEnergy(self, population: collections.abc.Sequence) -> List[float]: Normalize energy
class AFLGoSchedule: Assign high energy to seeds close to the target
assignEnergy(self, population: collections.abc.Sequence): Assigns each seed energy inversely proportional to the average function-level distance to target.
class DirectedSchedule: Assign high energy to seeds close to some target
__init__(self, distance: Dict[str, int], exponent: float) -> None: Constructor
__getFunctions__(self, coverage: Set[Location]) -> Set[str]
assignEnergy(self, population: collections.abc.Sequence) -> None: Assigns each seed energy inversely proportional to the average function-level distance to target.
class DictMutator: Variant of `Mutator` inserting keywords from a dictionary
__init__(self, dictionary: collections.abc.Sequence) -> None: Constructor. `dictionary` - a list of strings that can be used as keywords
insert_from_dictionary(self, s: str) -> str: Returns `s` with a keyword from the dictionary inserted
class Mutator: Mutate strings
__init__(self) -> None: Constructor
delete_random_character(self, s: str) -> str: Returns s with a random character deleted
flip_random_character(self, s: str) -> str: Returns s with a random bit flipped in a random position
insert_random_character(self, s: str) -> str: Returns s with a random character inserted
mutate(self, inp: Any) -> Any: Return s with a random mutation applied. Can be overloaded in subclasses.
class Seed: Represent an input with additional attributes
__init__(self, data: str) -> None: Initialize from seed data
__repr__(self) -> str: Returns data as string representation of the seed
__str__(self) -> str: Returns data as string representation of the seed
